    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for Ghost Ride the WHIP centers on exploiting high-ceiling matchups, led by **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, who clocks in as our highest-rated starter at 79.92. Facing Arrighetti, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** benefits from a weak opposing starter (xERA 5.10) and a massive 19% boost from the pitcher's skill profile, making him a locked-in core play. **James Wood** (73.18) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.54) round out our elite tier; **James Wood** leverages his leadoff spot against the shaky Hudson to provide volume in R and SB, while **Corbin Carroll** remains a perennial threat despite a neutral matchup against Michael King. **Tyler Soderstrom** also earns a strong recommendation (65.85), anchored by a favorable #3 slot in the order and a dynamic platoon advantage against Rocker that elevates his utility significantly.\n\nThe primary bench decision involved **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who narrowly missed the threshold with a 39.32 score. While his base projection is solid, the combination of a daunting matchup against the difficult Detmers and a significant 45% rain risk forced the model to keep him below our 40-point efficiency floor. Elsewhere, we are keeping a close eye on the wind reports; the favorable breeze out provides a tangible boost to **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Seiya Suzuki**, though **Seiya Suzuki** faces a tough test against the elite Wrobleski, whose 2.89 xERA severely caps his upside despite the park factors. Investors should note that while **Brice Turang** sits just below the 60-point \"Strong\" threshold at 58.63, his prime leadoff placement against Mlodzinski keeps him in the lineup, prioritizing the high-probability SB opportunities essential to our 5x5 strategy.",
